Description: modern, fast (high-performance) web framework (Avalan PPA pin)
 FastAPI is a Python web framework for building HTTP and WebSocket
 APIs on top of Starlette and Pydantic. Avalan ships it in its
 `server` extras at `>= 0.136.1, < 0.137`; Debian sid carries
 0.135.3 (below floor), so the rebuild lands at the pinned 0.136.1.
 .
 Runtime deps (starlette >= 0.46, pydantic >= 2.9, typing-extensions
 >= 4.8, typing-inspection >= 0.4.2, annotated-doc >= 0.0.2) come
 from a mix of Noble's archive (typing-extensions) and the Avalan
 PPA (starlette, pydantic, typing-inspection, annotated-doc).
